-- 
Crude Oil, Gasoline, Heating Oil Gain on Economy: Oil Products

-- B y   R i c h a r d   S t u b b e
-- 
2011-03-29T20:49:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/crude-oil-gasoline-heating-oil-gain-on-economy-oil-products.html
Crude oil , gasoline, heating oil
and ethanol advanced as a gain in U.S. equities signaled that
the economic recovery will accelerate, boosting demand for fuel.
The energy commodities rose as the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index
jumped 0.7 percent, its fourth increase in five days.  Crude Oil  Crude oil for May delivery rose 81 cents, or 0.8 percent,
to $104.79 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . Crude
has gained 28 percent in the past year.  “We’re seeing equities move higher, and that’s giving a
little bit of positive sentiment toward crude,” said  Matt Smith , a commodities analyst for Summit Energy Services Inc. in
Louisville, Kentucky.  Gasoline  Gasoline for April delivery increased 1.84 cents, or 0.6
percent, to $3.0458 a gallon on the Nymex, the highest
settlement in three weeks. Gasoline has gained 35 percent in the
past year.  Heating Oil  Heating oil for April delivery advanced 1.66 cents, or 0.5
percent, to settle at $3.0415 a gallon on the Nymex. Heating oil
has gained 44 percent in a year.  Ethanol  Denatured ethanol for April delivery rose 0.7 cent to
$2.492 a gallon on the Chicago Board of Trade. Ethanol has
increased 59 percent in the past year.  Refineries and Transport  Valero Energy Corp. (VLO)  is starting planned maintenance at the
Corpus Christi West refinery in Texas, according to two filings
with state regulators. The work isn’t expected to affect
production, Bill Day, a spokesman based at company headquarters
in  San Antonio , said in an e-mail.  Sunoco Inc. (SUN)  began returning units to service at its Marcus
Hook refinery in Pennsylvania after some were shut following a
power failure. At 8:30 p.m. yesterday, Sunoco informed the
Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection that “all
units were coming back online.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
